Token.Abstract: Returns a shared instance of this service client using [AWSServiceManager defaultServiceManager].defaultServiceConfiguration. When defaultServiceConfiguration is not set, this method returns nil.

ReturnValue.Abstract: A shared instance of this service client.

Parameter.Name: key
Parameter.Abstract: A string to identify the service client.

Parameter.Name: key
Parameter.Abstract: A string to identify the service client.

ReturnValue.Abstract: An instance of the service client.

Parameter.Name: key
Parameter.Abstract: A string to identify the service client.

Token.Abstract: Invokes an AWS Lambda function with a given request object.

ReturnValue.Abstract: An instance of AWSTask. On successful execution, task.result will contain an instance of AWSLambdaInvokerInvocationResponse. On failed service execution, task.error may contain an NSError with AWSLambdaErrorDomain domain and the following error code: AWSLambdaErrorService, AWSLambdaErrorResourceNotFound, AWSLambdaErrorInvalidParameterValue. On failed function execution, task.error may contain an NSError with AWSLambdaInvokerErrorDomain domain and the following error code: AWSLambdaInvokerErrorTypeFunctionError.

Token.Abstract: Invokes an AWS Lambda function with a given request object.

Parameter.Name: completionHandler
Parameter.Abstract: The completion handler to call when the invoke request is complete. response - An AWSLambdaInvokerInvocationResponse object, or nil if the request failed. error - An error object that indicates why the request failed, or nil if the request was successful. On failed service execution, task.error may contain an NSError with AWSLambdaErrorDomain domain and the following error code: AWSLambdaErrorService, AWSLambdaErrorResourceNotFound, AWSLambdaErrorInvalidParameterValue. On failed function execution, task.error may contain an NSError with AWSLambdaInvokerErrorDomain domain and the following error code: AWSLambdaInvokerErrorTypeFunctionError.

Token.Abstract: Invokes a synchronous AWS Lambda function with given parameters.

Parameter.Name: JSONObject
Parameter.Abstract: The object from which to generate JSON request data. Can be nil.

ReturnValue.Abstract: An instance of AWSTask. On successful execution, task.result will contain a JSON object. On failed service execution, task.error may contain an NSError with AWSLambdaErrorDomain domain and the following error code: AWSLambdaErrorService, AWSLambdaErrorResourceNotFound, AWSLambdaErrorInvalidParameterValue. On failed function execution, task.error may contain an NSError with AWSLambdaInvokerErrorDomain domain and the following error code: AWSLambdaInvokerErrorTypeFunctionError.

Token.Abstract: Invokes a synchronous AWS Lambda function with given parameters.
